# Metro Civic public template compliance deck / turn1

Using the seed deck, template_rules.txt, style_reference.svg, layout_grid.svg, and metro_civic_seal.png, convert the rough Metro Civic Grants notes into a two-slide editable PowerPoint briefing that follows the strict public template. Every slide must use the navy #112A4A header and footer bands, the Metro Civic seal in the upper-left header, and the footer text "PUBLIC TEMPLATE • Metro Civic Grants Office • Confidential draft". Slide 1 must be titled "Metro Civic Grants: FY26 Oversight", use the teal all-caps section band "PROGRAM STATUS BRIEFING", and place three aligned status cards labeled "Program health", "Funding status", and "Timeline" across the top row inside the template grid. Include the panels "Risk watch" and "Council checkpoint" below the cards. Slide 2 must use the section band "COMPLIANCE MONITORING" and include an editable compliance table with the headers "Area", "Status", "Owner", and "Next step" plus the rows for Reporting, Procurement, and Equity review. Preserve exactly the protected legal notice "Protected legal notice: FY26 allocations remain preliminary until council adoption." and the audit sentinel "Do not edit: Metro Civic audit trail invariant." without moving them into content regions.

